# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020099> (bravais lattice (3D))

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020099> "TODO: possibly extend for 2D (Graphene etc)

More elaborate crystal descriptions may be found in http://emmo.info/domain-crystallography/crystallography or https://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/disos/cso"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020099> "bravais lattice (3D)"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020099> "The bravais lattice is a categorical value specification that specifies value of the crystal structure quality. It describes the possible geometric arrangement of lattice points in a crystal. The present descriptor is limited to the 14 possible three-dimensional arrangements."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020099> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020099> ObjectOneOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020007> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020008> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020009> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020010> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020011> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020012> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020013> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020014> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020015> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020016> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020017> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020018> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020019>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020099> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001930>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101> (proportion)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101> "proportion"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101> "concentration"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101> "fraction"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101> "A proportion is a relational quality between two entities (the whole and the part) which quantifies the relation between the whole and its part."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000145>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020102> (mass proportion)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020102> "mass proportion"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020102> "Mass proportion is a proportion which quantifies the mass of the part relative to the mass of the whole."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020102> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020102> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020103> (molar proportion)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020103> "molar proportion"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020103> "Molar Ratio"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020103> "Molar proportion is the proportion which quantifies the entities count of the part in relation to the entities count of the whole."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020103> "The molar ratio of hydrogen gas H2 molecules to water H2O molecules is 1/1 in the oxyhydrogen reaction. The molar ratio of oxygen molecules O2 to water molecules is 2/1.
The molar ratio of carbon dioxide to average atmosphere air is 420 ppm as of 2022 AD."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020103> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020103> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020104> (volume proportion)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020104> "volume proportion"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020104> "Volume proportion is a proportion which quantifies the volume of the part relative to the volume of the whole."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020104> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020104> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020106> (polycrystal)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020106> "polycrystal"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020106> "Polycrystalline structure"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020106> "A polycrystal is a connected material entity aggregate that consists of multiple crystal grains joined through crystallographic interfaces."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020106> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020106> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000890>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020106> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000663>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020112> (grain size distribution)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020112> "grain size distribution"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020112> "An intensive quality describing the lower length scale object aggregate (grains) that is part of the material."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020112> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020112> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020116> (aggregate state value)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020116> "aggregate state value"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020116> "The aggregate state value is a categorical value specification that specifies value of the aggregate state quality."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020116> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020116> ObjectOneOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020117> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020118> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020120> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020121> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020122> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020123> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020124> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020125>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020116> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001930>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020128> (thermodynamic system)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020128> "thermodynamic system"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020128> "A thermodynamic system is an object aggregate whose objects are bearer of  thermodynamic properties. A thermodynamic system environs a thermodynamic process by which the thermodynamic properties of the objects of the thermodynamic system change over time."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020128> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020128> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> (intensive quality)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> "intensive quality"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> "Point property"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> "An intensive quality is a quality that inheres in only portion of matter and thus is independent of the bearers (system-) size."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000019>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000080> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000001>))
SubClassOf(Annotation(rdfs:comment "Due to the duality of object and portion of matter this axiom can not be an equivalent class axiom."@en) <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000080> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000001>))
DisjointClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020132> (size)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020132> "size"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020132> "an extensive quality of a material entity that describes its spatial extend."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020132> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020132> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020133> (mass)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020133> "Mass is relevant in such processes as gravitation, acceleration, etc."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020133> "mass"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020133> "Mass is fundamental extensive quality."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020133> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020133> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020136> (phase transformation)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020136> "The number of phases involved can vary as well as the mechanisms involved can be different."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020136> "phase transformation"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020136> "A thermodynamic phase transformation is a process in/of a thermodynamic system, that involves the transformation of phases of the system to other phases."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020136> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020136> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020137> (stable phase)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020137> "See metastable phase"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020137> "stable phase"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020137> "A stable phase is a phase that does not have a \"pmd:disposition of a phase to transform\" in the \"pmd:phase transformation\" it participates."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020137> "A phase that participates in a phase transformation pt and pt that is not a metastable phase."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020137> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020137> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020000>)
DisjointClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020137> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020149>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020140> (portion of pure chemical element)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020140> "portion of pure chemical element"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020140> "A portion of pure chemical element is a pure substance composed of multiple atoms, which are all of the same kind."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020140> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_60003>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020142> (energy)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020142> <http://openenergy-platform.org/ontology/oeo/OEO_00000150>)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020142> "energy"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020142> "an extensive quality of material entities which manifests as a capacity to perform work (such as causing motion or the interaction of molecules)"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020142> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020142> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020143> (process chain)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020143> "process chain"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020143> "A process chain is a process that 'has continuant part' subprocesses S1...Sn where S1...Sn precede each other and where some object or object aggregate that are output of Sn are then input to Sn+1."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020143> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148> (extensive quality)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148> "extensive quality"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148> "An extensive quality is a quality that inheres in only object or object aggregate or fiat object part or chemical entity and is dependent on the bearers (system-) size."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000019>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020149> (metastable phase)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020149> "The stability of a phase can only be evaluated in the context of a (possibly unknown) phase transformation process."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020149> "metastable phase"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020149> "A metastable phase phase_trans is a phase that has a \"pmd:disposition of a phase to transform\" disp_trans and disp_trans is realized in a \"pmd:phase transformation\" proc_trans and proc_trans has participant sys_trans and sys_trans has part phase_trans."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020149> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020149> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020000>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020161> (activity (thermodynamic))

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020161> "old defintion: 
Activity (a_X) is a relational property between a chemical species X and a non-ideal solution. a_X is a measure of the effective concentration of a chemical species X in the non-ideal solution, accounting for interactions between particles. It is defined as the product of the concentration and an activity coefficient, where the activity coefficient corrects for non-ideal behavior.")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020161> "activity (thermodynamic)"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020161> "Thermodynamic activity is a relational quality that inheres between a chemical species and a non-ideal solution and represents the effective concentration of the species accounting for particle interactions."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020161> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000145>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020201> (section)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020201> "section"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020201> "Section is a planar fiat surface cutting across the object"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020201> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000146>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020207> (amount of substance)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020207> "amount of substance"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020207> "Amount of substance n is a molar proportion when the whole is an object aggregate N, which has avogadro number objects (of same type) as parts (n = N/N_A)."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020207> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020103>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020210> (elemental crystal)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020210> "elemental crystal"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020210> "a crystal that consists of exactly one atomic species"@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020210> ObjectExactCardinality(1 <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002351> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020140>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020210> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020003>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020210> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002351> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020140>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020216> (order scale value)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020216> "order scale value"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020216> "possible values of characteristic length over which structural correlations persist in a material"@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020216> ObjectOneOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020217> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020218> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020219> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020242>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020216> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001930>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020220> (order scale)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020220> "order scale"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020220> "characteristic length over which structural correlations persist in a material"@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020220> ObjectExactCardinality(1 <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020216>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020220> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020220> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020216>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020243> (grain size)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020243> "size values of indiviudal grains are properties of the respective objects"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020243> "grain size"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020243> "an intensive quality epitomizing the average size of the grains of a polycrystal"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020243> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020243> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000080> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020106>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025001> (composition)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025001> "There's a dfference between composition and chemical compositon for the following reason: chemical compositon is relevant when the mass/volume/mole proportions of chemical elements(!) are identified, whlist composition includes proportions of molecules, other pure chemical substances, or even proptions of objects (in an object aggregate)."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025001> "composition"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025001> "Composition is an intensive quality which defines types and proportions of compounds present in a material entity and is subject of some composition data item."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025001> "4 vol.% nitric acid solution, Styrene-Butadiene-Styrene (SBS) Block Copolymer with 50 vol.% of both styrene and butadiene"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025001> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000064> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025001> "Composition is a collective property of a portion of matter, i.e., the triple portion of matter has quality composition holds. As \"has quality\" is an inverse  functional property, only one instance of portion of matter can have this specific composition. However, proportions describe the relation between the prortion of matter (the whole) and some compound (the part). Thus, the following triples hold: portion of matter has relational quality proportion; portion of matter has part some substance (or whatever is your part); substance has relational quality proportion. \"Has relational quality\" is not inverse functional, i.e., it can point to a single object from 2 distinct subjects."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025001> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025002> (chemical composition data item)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025002> "chemical composition data item"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025002> "chemical composition specification"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025002> "Chemical composition data item is an information content entity that is about composition of a portion of matter. It has members fraction value specifications which specifiy values of propotions of portions of (pure) chemical elements, which are parts of the portion of matter."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025002> "Steel has quality chemical composition , and the chemical composition data item is about the chemical composition .The chemical composition data item has members fraction specifications of iron and carbon. These fraction specifications specify value of portion of iron and portion of carbon respectively. Furthermore, these fraction specifications specify  values of relational qualities (mass) proportion of iron and (mass) proportion of carbon."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025002> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025002> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020004> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000136> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000551>)))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025003> (metallic grain structure)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025003> "ferrite, austenite, martensite, etc."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025003> "metallic grain structure"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025003> "intensive quality epitomizing the distinct phases in the microscopic structure of a metallic material."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025003> "false"^^xsd:boolean)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025003> ObjectExactCardinality(1 <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020023>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025003> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025003> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020023>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025007> (frequency)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025007> "frequency"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025007> "Frequency is a process attribute which characterizes the rate per second of oscillation or vibration."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025007> "Frequency of electromagnetic wave, Frequency of sound wave."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025007> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000008>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025008> (Transmissionselektronenmikroskop)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025008> "Transmissionselektronenmikroskop"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025008> "transmission electron microscope"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025008> "An electron microscope that produces high-resolution images of a sample's internal structure by transmitting electrons through the sample."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025008> "Ein Elektronenmikroskop, das hochauflösende Bilder der inneren Struktur einer Probe erzeugt, indem es Elektronen durch die Probe strahlt."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025008> "TEM")
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025008> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000624>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025012> (analytical calculation)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025012> "analytical calculation"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025012> "Analytical calculation is a computing process which has value specification or measurement datum as a specified output. It applies a closed-form mathematical expression or formula to a set it specified inputs (value specifications) without requiring stochastic sampling, iterative numerical solving, or data-driven training."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025012> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000583>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025015> (portion of lanthanum)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025015> "'portion of pure chemical element' and 'has part' only CHEBI:33336"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025015> "portion of lanthanum"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025015> "A portion of lanthanum is a portion of pure substance that has parts only chebi:lanthanum atom."@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025015> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020140> ObjectAllValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_33336>)))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025015> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020140>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025997> (fraction value specification)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025997> "fraction value specification"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025997> "Fraction value specification is a value specification that contains information about quantitative share of a part relative to a specified whole."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025997> "2.05 wt.% of carbon in steel, 4 vol.% of nitric acid in a solution"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025997> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001931>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025997> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001927> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020101> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025999> ObjectIntersectionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000040> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000040>))))))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025997> ObjectAllValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002350> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020004>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> (length)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> "Length is a size that describes the spatial extent of its bearer in one dimension."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> "length"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> "dimension"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> "Length is a one dimensional size."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020132>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050051> (Durchmesser)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050051> "“Diameter.” Merriam-Webster.com Dictionary, Merriam-Webster, https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/diameter. Accessed 5 Dec. 2022.")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050051> "Durchmesser"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050051> "diameter"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050051> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/2.0.8/Diameter>)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050051> "Die Länge einer geraden Linie durch den Mittelpunkt eines Objekts oder Raums."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050051> "The length of a straight line through the center of an object or space."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050051> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050155> (shape)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050155> "“Shape.” Merriam-Webster.com Dictionary, Merriam-Webster, https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/shape. Accessed 13 Jan. 2023.")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050155> "Form"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050155> "shape"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050155> "Das sichtbare Ausstattungsmerkmal (räumliche Form oder Kontur) eines bestimmten Objektes oder einer Art von Objekt."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050155> "Extemsive quality, the visible makeup characteristic (spatial form or contour) of a particular item or kind of item."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050155> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050156> (Geometrische Form)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050156> "DIN EN ISO 6892-1:2019")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050156> "Geometrische Form"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050156> "geometry shape"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050156> "Dieses Konzept beschreibt die geometrischen Abmessungen und das Erscheinungsbild (Form und Abmaße) einer Probe, eines Prüfkörpers oder eines Prüfstücks, wie sie üblicherweise durch eine entsprechende Norm definiert sind. Dementsprechend ist der angegebene Formwert in Übereinstimmung mit der definierenden Norm anzugeben, z. B. \"Zugprüfstück Form 1 gemäß Anhang B der Zugversuchsnorm\"."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050156> "This concept describes the geometric dimensions and appearance (shape and dimensions) of a sample, specimen, or test piece as usually defined by a corresponding standard. Accordingly, the shape value given is in accordance with the defining standard, e.g., ‘tensile test piece shape 1 in accordance with annex B of the tensile test standard’."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050156> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050155>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050157> (3D Geometrie)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050157> "3D Geometrie"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050157> "shape 3d"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050157> "A shape 3D is a geometry shape that exists in three dimensions, having length, width, and height, and can be defined by its spatial properties such as volume and surface area."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050157> "Eine 3D Geometrie ist eine geometrische Form, die in drei Dimensionen existiert, mit Länge, Breite und Höhe, und die durch ihre räumlichen Eigenschaften wie Volumen und Oberfläche definiert werden kann."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050157> "Beispiele sind Formen wie Würfel, Kugeln und Pyramiden."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050157> "Examples include shapes like cubes, spheres, and pyramids."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050157> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050156>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000000> (unit cell)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000000> "unit cell"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000000> "Unit cell is a site which is a part of a crystal lattice and represents the smallest volume, from which the lattice can be constructed by translational displacements. Unit cell is characterized by the length of its sides and their angular relations."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000000> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000029>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000001> (crystal lattice)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000001> "TODO: 
1. check if located in is meant to be used this way
2. Is there a better alternative to has part?"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000001> "crystal lattice"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000001> "Crystal lattice is a site which has unit cell as part and is location of a crystal. It represents a periodic array of points in space, which describe the arrangement of atoms or molecules in a crystal."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000001> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000029>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000001> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000000>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000001> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0001015> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020003>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000002> (lattice parameter)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000002> "lattice parameter"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000002> "Lattice parameter is a quality of a unit cell which describes the length of (three) dimensions along of thwe unit cell's x-, y-, and z-directions."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000002> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000002> ObjectAllValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000080> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000000>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000003> (a lattice parameter)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000003> "a lattice parameter"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000003> "A length of a unit cell along its x-axis"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000003> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000002>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000004> (b lattice parameter)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000004> "b lattice parameter"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000004> "A length of a unit cell along its y-axis"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000004> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000002>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000005> (c lattice parameter)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000005> "c lattice parameter"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000005> "A length of a unit cell along its z-axis"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000005> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000002>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000006> (angular lattice parameter)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000006> "TODO check the naming conventions")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000006> "angular lattice parameter"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000006> "Angular lattice parameter is a relational quality between two axes in a unit cell"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000006> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000145>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000006> ObjectAllValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000080> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000000>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000007> (α lattice parameter)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000007> "α lattice parameter"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000007> "α lattice parameter is an anlge between y- and z-directions in a unit cell"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000007> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000006>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000008> (β lattice parameter)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000008> "β lattice parameter"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000008> "β lattice parameter is an anlge between x- and z-directions in a unit cell"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000008> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000006>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000009> (γ lattice parameter)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000009> "γ lattice parameter"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000009> "γ lattice parameter is an anlge between x- and z-directions in a unit cell"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000009> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000006>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000010> (basis)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000010> "basis"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000010> "Basis is a object aggregate which has one or more atoms or molecules as parts. It defines the minimal number of atoms or molecules to form a unit cell."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000010> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000010> ObjectAllValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0001025> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000000>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000011> (crystallographic plane)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000011> "crystallographic plane"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000011> "Crystallographic plane is a fiat surface which is part of a crystal lattice and which is denoted by Miller indices of a plane."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000011> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000146>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000011> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000001>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000012> (crystallographic direction)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000012> "crystallographic direction"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000012> "Crystallographic direction is a fiat line which is part of a crystal lattice and which is denoted by Miller indices of a direction."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000012> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000142>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000012> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000001>))

